      "writtenOn": "2016-11-11T19:14:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The logic here isn\u0027t quite foolproof, but:\n\n1) If you\u0027re rendering to a color correct GPU-backed surface, then you had to be able to create a surface that was either sRGB or F16 (we sanity check config + color space combinations at surface creation).\n\n2) Nothing prevents you from indirectly calling this code without a valid surface to draw to, though - so that logic is only partially valid. It\u0027s probably wiser to be really explicit, and fall back to legacy when everything else fails. Maybe I can find a way to simplify the logic here - it\u0027s pretty gnarly.",
      "parentUuid": "eb935fd8_e4478bba",
